The paper focuses on video object detection from a robotic perspective, which suggests that it is likely to fall under the Robotics (cs.RO) category. The paper also deals with computer vision techniques such as object detection and tracking, which makes Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) another likely category. The paper proposes non-reference assessments and online tracklet refinement, which suggests that it may also belong to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. Finally, the paper conducts experiments on real-world robotic tasks, which suggests that it may also fall under Multimedia (cs.MM) category.
